6:
Um, sorry, could you tell me where
to carry this stuff?
9:
Nn? Oh, don't worry about that,
Clara! I'll take care of it!
15:
Shhh. Just stand back and leave the
heavy lifting to us, girlie.
22:
Bahaha! That "girlie" could bench
press an anchor! Clara's tougher'n
any of the crew— me included, I'd
reckon.
23:
That aside, we could use some extra
muscle for our next shipment. You in,
Clara?
29:
*sigh* That'll be another week of
dealing with these drunken louts,
huh?
35:
I know I can't afford to be picky with
jobs, but a girl can dream.
36:
Why do they even hire me if they're
just gonna act like I can't do my job.
Mercenary work isn't exactly stable,
either...
38:
Long as it puts bread on the table, I
guess I can't complain, though.
40: You should be ashamed of yourself!
47:
Extorting money from a child?! Have
you no honor?
50:
Look, bun, this here's my dock. If the
kid wants to use, he's gotta pay the
toll like anyone else.
53: It most certainly is not your dock.
55:
As I understand, the Floatdwellers
long since rejected feudal holdings.
This land belongs to all!
56:
I will not stand for highway robbery
in a world which touts liberty and
free trade!
59: Restrain the rabbit. I'll deal with—
69:
Blasted beast... Better hope you can
pay, or I'll—
73:
Geez, I'm SOOO clumsy! I dropped
my axe!
76: You two are lucky it didn't hit you.
79:
Sh-she threw an axe that big f-from
the other side of the ship...
80:
You know what, we've got uh...
places to be!
85:
You have my gratitude, mercenary.
It was not my intention to cause a
scene.
90: No problem! *sigh* You were so cool!
98:
That speech of yours was really
inspiring! I felt braver just watching
you stand up to those thugs.
103: Thank you for saving Light, Clara.
108:
I'm ashamed I couldn't handle the
situation myself.
112:
All's well that ends well. I'm glad
neither of you are hurt.
114:
I'm truly sorry. If I hadn't run my
mouth...
118: Relax, Light. No one's mad at you.
120:
I know, but all the same. I should
know by now that I cannot defend
myself in this form, and yet I still
acted rashly.
125:
Aw, that's okay. You were super
brave! I've never seen someone so
dashing!
130:
I'll bet. That's our bunny in shining
armor!
136:
I was tossed face-first into the
ground! That's not—
142:
All right, enough. Clara, you asked if
we had any work for a mercenary,
right?
146:
Yes. Hearing that you're setting sail
for distant lands, I thought it'd be a
good change of pace.
148:
I'm stronger than I look, so I'm sure I
can make myself useful somehow.
154:
I don't doubt your abilities, but are
you certain you'd like to join us?
159:
We're, uh... Let's just say our
adventures aren't the most
lucrative, so you might be better off
sticking to the docks.
163:
That's okay. I'd rather work with
people I believe in—people I know
who'll push me to be my best self!
173:
We'd be glad to have you with us,
Clara. Welcome to the team.
178:
Aye aye, captain! Thank you so
much!
